==Latin==

===Etymology===
In post-classical Latin (4th or 5th century) in reference to a sum of money due each year.
Already in the 3rd century in the sense of "through the year". From the preposition {{m|la|per||during}} + {{m|la|annum|}}, the accusative singular of {{m|la|annus||year}}.

